Useful basic vim commands

*To learn about vim - "Tutor"

1.Cursor moving- "either arrow keys" or "hjkl"

2.Insert mode- "i"
3.Normal mode- "esc"
4.save and exit - ":wq" exit without saving- "q"

5.Deleting single letters pointed in cursor- "x"
6.Deleting words - "dw"
7.Deleting whole lines- "dd"

8.Undo deleted - "u"

9.To get shell in vim - ":!(commands)"

10.To select words,lines - "v"

11. To paste selected words - "p"

